    ],
    "summary": "On 17-Nov-2015 at approximately 0700 hours, a contract worker experienced chemical exposure to Tretolite DM0484X demulsifier while working on a chemical injection pump at W&T Offshore's High Island 110 'A' platform. The worker knelt on a rag saturated with the demulsifier, causing a chemical burn to his left knee. Initial first aid was provided on site, but the burn worsened over two days. The worker was sent for medical evaluation and treatment, resulting in restricted duty for approximately 16 days.",
